"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-brainstorm-2024-0722-1461186-paris-1924-olympic-stadium-history-stade-de-colombes-stade-yves-du-manoir\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Analysis: Stade de Colombes is the only facility from 100 years ago that will host events at this summer's games in Paris  ByRuadh\\u00e1n Cooke,University of Galway  The opening ceremony ofthis year's Olympic Gameswill take place on the River Seine in the centre of the French capital.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 280, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 116, \"end\": 121, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.601480117628503e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 232, \"end\": 243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 265, \"end\": 271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9995446284145046, \"rank\": 0.00045378131439508933, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris previously hostedthe second Gamesof the modern era on the fringes of the Universal Exhibition of 1900, and again inthe summer of 1924.\", \"from\": 281, \"to\": 421, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 281, \"end\": 286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.601480117628503e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the 100th anniversary of the 1924 Games, the first Olympics at which a 48-strong team of 46 men and 2 womenfrom the recently independent Irish Free Statecompeted as Ireland, what tangible legacy of the Games immortalised in the filmChariots of Fireendures?\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 591, \"end\": 598, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999479028521374, \"rank\": 4.774676207168495e-05, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What remains of the stadium lit up by the exploits of British athletesHarold AbrahamsandEric Liddelland the Flying Finn,Paavo Nurmi?\", \"from\": 683, \"to\": 815, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 737, \"end\": 744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9905942697070345, \"rank\": 0.009493781218150742, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 791, \"end\": 802, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flying_Finn\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.112396942896869e-39, \"text\": \"Flying Finn\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flying_Finn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flying_Finn\"}, {\"begin\": 803, \"end\": 814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paavo_Nurmi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paavo Nurmi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paavo_Nurmi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paavo_Nurmi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From Olympics, Paavo Nurmi, the nine-time Olympic champ you have probably never heard of  In light of the burgeoning popular interest in the coverage of sporting events, the national daily newspaperLe Matindeveloped theStade du Matinstadium in 1907 in the northwestern Parisian suburb of Colombes on the site of a horse racing track first opened in 1883.Racing Club de France, a socially exclusive multi-sports club founded in 1882, acquired the lease to the renamed Stade de Colombes in 1919, by which time it had already become a leading venue for athletics meetings and football and rugby matches.\", \"from\": 819, \"to\": 1419, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 834, \"end\": 845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paavo_Nurmi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paavo Nurmi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paavo_Nurmi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paavo_Nurmi\"}, {\"begin\": 1173, \"end\": 1194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Racing_92\", \"score\": 0.8329094015255487, \"rank\": 0.20060962544548358, \"text\": \"Racing Club de France\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Racing_92\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Racing_92\"}, {\"begin\": 1286, \"end\": 1303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Yves-du-Manoir\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de Colombes\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Yves-du-Manoir\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Yves-du-Manoir\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France was admitted to rugby'sFive Nations Championshipin 1910 and hosted Ireland for the first time at the Stade de Colombes on April 9th 1921, the previous games having taken place in theParc des Princes(which will host some of this summer's football matches).\", \"from\": 1420, \"to\": 1682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1420, \"end\": 1426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9150918029652009, \"rank\": 0.07326736841291735, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1494, \"end\": 1501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999479028521374, \"rank\": 4.774676207168495e-05, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two years out from the 1924 Olympic Games, Paris still had no stadium suitable for an international event of this scale.\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1804, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1727, \"end\": 1732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.601480117628503e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With the support of public funds, Racing Club agreed to redevelop its facility and a state-of-the-art Olympic Stadium at Colombes was officially opened on May 4th 1924    United States vs France in 1924 Olympics rugby final  On that day, France defeated Romania in the Olympic rugby tournament, which comprised of only three nations.\", \"from\": 1805, \"to\": 2138, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1839, \"end\": 1850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Racing_92\", \"score\": 0.9999935477811842, \"rank\": 6.4522605876401124e-06, \"text\": \"Racing Club\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Racing_92\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Racing_92\"}, {\"begin\": 1976, \"end\": 1989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9275437860745318, \"rank\": 0.052629175626705806, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1993, \"end\": 1999, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9150918029652009, \"rank\": 0.07326736841291735, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2043, \"end\": 2049, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9150918029652009, \"rank\": 0.07326736841291735, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2059, \"end\": 2066, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999288884308, \"rank\": 6.934892078071695e-08, \"text\": \"Romania\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As defending champions from the 1920 Games, the United States had a bye to the final where they easily accounted for France in a match marred by violence and nicknamed the\\\"Corrida of Colombes\\\".\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2332, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2187, \"end\": 2200, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9275437860745318, \"rank\": 0.052629175626705806, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2256, \"end\": 2262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9150918029652009, \"rank\": 0.07326736841291735, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Partly as a consequence, rugby was removed from the Olympic programme.\", \"from\": 2333, \"to\": 2403, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rugby Sevens became an Olympic sport in 2016 at theRio Gamesand Ireland will be represented by both a women's and men's team in Paris this year.\", \"from\": 2404, \"to\": 2548, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2404, \"end\": 2416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rugby_sevens\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.936082469408265e-21, \"text\": \"Rugby Sevens\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rugby_sevens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rugby_sevens\"}, {\"begin\": 2468, \"end\": 2475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999479028521374, \"rank\": 4.774676207168495e-05, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 2532, \"end\": 2537, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.601480117628503e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although a number of events likeart, rugby and football took place outside of the main window, theopening ceremonywas held on Saturday, 5 July 1924 in the Olympic Stadium, which hosted the full athletics programme, cycling road race, gymnastics, some equestrian competitions, lawn tennis, rugby, football and a number of demonstration events.\", \"from\": 2550, \"to\": 2892, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2801, \"end\": 2811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"score\": 0.9966751774174641, \"rank\": 0.0033359136176239813, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Irish competitors took part in football, art, athletics, boxing, lawn tennis and water polo.\", \"from\": 2893, \"to\": 2985, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2893, \"end\": 2898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999019797927554, \"rank\": 5.961874378382192e-05, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Significant firsts for the Games were wireless radio broadcasts, an official closing ceremony and an athletes' village.\", \"from\": 2987, \"to\": 3106, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the aftermath, the stadium became France's de facto national stadium hosting rugby and football internationals, including the final of the1938 FIFA World Cup.\", \"from\": 3107, \"to\": 3268, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3144, \"end\": 3150, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9150918029652009, \"rank\": 0.07326736841291735, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3253, \"end\": 3257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\", \"score\": 0.9999971328875464, \"rank\": 2.867120249272037e-06, \"text\": \"FIFA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\"}, {\"begin\": 3258, \"end\": 3267, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA_World_Cup\", \"score\": 0.9998263904219269, \"rank\": 0.00016211508295221685, \"text\": \"World Cup\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA_World_Cup\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA_World_Cup\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1928 the stadium was renamedStade Olympique Yves du Manoir.\", \"from\": 3270, \"to\": 3332, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This was in memory of du Manoir, the Racing Club member, French rugby international and military aviator who had been killed that year in a plane accident.\", \"from\": 3333, \"to\": 3488, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3370, \"end\": 3381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Racing_92\", \"score\": 0.9999935477811842, \"rank\": 6.4522605876401124e-06, \"text\": \"Racing Club\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Racing_92\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Racing_92\"}, {\"begin\": 3390, \"end\": 3396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9995446284145046, \"rank\": 0.00045378131439508933, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Incidentally, du Manoir won the first of his 8 caps when selected at out-half against Ireland at Colombes on New Year's Day 1925.\", \"from\": 3489, \"to\": 3618, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3575, \"end\": 3582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999479028521374, \"rank\": 4.774676207168495e-05, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With redevelopment of theParc des Princes in 1972, Colombes was relegated from French sport's centre-stage.\", \"from\": 3620, \"to\": 3727, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3699, \"end\": 3705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9995446284145046, \"rank\": 0.00045378131439508933, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, with some refurbishments over the decades, it most notably became the home ground of the Top 14 rugby franchiseRacing 92before the club relocated in late 2017 to theLa D\\u00e9fense Arena, a venue hosting the 2024 swimming events in which Irish interest will be strong.\", \"from\": 3728, \"to\": 4000, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3970, \"end\": 3975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999019797927554, \"rank\": 5.961874378382192e-05, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Owned since 2002 by thelocal authority for the Hauts-de-Seine(number 92 in the list of France's 96d\\u00e9partements), the Colombes complex has undergone extensive renovations and is the only facility from 100 years ago that will once again host events at this summer's games, when it will be the venue for the full field hockey programme.\", \"from\": 4002, \"to\": 4335, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4089, \"end\": 4095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9150918029652009, \"rank\": 0.07326736841291735, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Saturday next, the Irish men's team begins its campaign against Pool B opponents Belgium on Pitch 2 of the Yves du Manoir Stadium.\", \"from\": 4337, \"to\": 4470, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4359, \"end\": 4364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999019797927554, \"rank\": 5.961874378382192e-05, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 4421, \"end\": 4428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.5617024459225949, \"rank\": 0.7802655218978614, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When the Games conclude, the stadium will become the headquarters and centre of excellence for theFrench Hockey Federation.\", \"from\": 4471, \"to\": 4594, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"True to its original vocation, the complex will also accommodate rugby and football.\", \"from\": 4595, \"to\": 4679, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A number of venues that hosted events at the 1924 Games are still in use today and some will facilitate competing teams for training purposes this summer.\", \"from\": 4681, \"to\": 4835, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This included theGeorges Vallerey swimming pool, whereJohnny Weissmuller, later ofTarzanfame, won three gold and a bronze medal for the United States in 1924.\", \"from\": 4836, \"to\": 4994, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4972, \"end\": 4985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9275437860745318, \"rank\": 0.052629175626705806, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Weissmuller competed at theTailteann Games in Dublina few weeks later, winning his swimming event held in the pond atDublin Zoo!\", \"from\": 4995, \"to\": 5123, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From RT\\u00c9 News, Paris mayor takes a pre-Olympics dip in the Seine to show it's clean  Leaving aside issues relating to water quality in the Seine which could potentially jeopardise the open-water swimming events (Mayor of Paris,Anne Hidalgo, and chair of the Organising Committee,Tony Estanguet, hada high-profile swimin the Seine last week) and a number of mini-controversies, delivery of facilities for Paris 2024 has been on time and within budget.\", \